f the Shitou line and various houses during the late Tang and Five Dynasties periods. Jia refutes the traditional Chan genealogy of two lines and five houses and calls for new frameworks in the study of Chan history. An annotated translation of datable discourses of Mazu is also included.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aHongzhou (Sect)xHistory. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / Sacred Writings.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780791481424?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791481424423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791481424/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles